The paper discusses the design of eventually consistent replication systems, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The focus is on registers, which are a type of data structure commonly used in databases (cs.DB) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also proposes a conflict resolution template, which involves application logic and semantics, making it relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
